---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="Commercial Door Upgrade Guide | Top Notch Doors & Windows"
  description="Learn what to look for when upgrading your commercial doors — steel, aluminum, automatic options. Expert advice from Top Notch Doors & Windows in Fort Lauderdale."
>
  <!-- Blog Hero -->
  <section class="relative bg-primary text-white py-16 md:py-20">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 text-center">
      <p class="text-gray-300 text-sm mb-2">March 5, 2026</p>
      <h1 class="font-heading text-4xl md:text-5xl tracking-wide">New Commercial Doors: What to Look For When Upgrading Your Business Entrance</h1>
    </div>
  </section>

  <article class="py-16 bg-white">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 prose prose-lg">
      <p class="text-gray-600 text-lg leading-relaxed">
        When it comes to your business, first impressions matter — and nothing makes a stronger first impression than your front entrance.
      </p>

      <h2 class="font-heading text-3xl tracking-wide text-primary mt-10 mb-4">Why Upgrade Your Commercial Doors?</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">
        Commercial doors experience significant wear from daily foot traffic and weather exposure. New installations provide improved insulation, modern locking systems, ADA compliance, and enhanced professional appearance.
      </p>

      <h2 class="font-heading text-3xl tracking-wide text-primary mt-10 mb-4">Types of Commercial Doors to Consider</h2>

      <h3 class="font-heading text-2xl tracking-wide text-primary mt-8 mb-3">Steel Entry Doors</h3>
      <p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">
        Superior strength and security, excellent insulation, low maintenance, and long lifespan suitable for warehouses, retail, and offices.
      </p>

      <h3 class="font-heading text-2xl tracking-wide text-primary mt-8 mb-3">Aluminum Glass Doors</h3>
      <p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">
        Maximize natural light with a modern aesthetic, high customer visibility, customizable with frosted or tinted glass options.
      </p>

      <h3 class="font-heading text-2xl tracking-wide text-primary mt-8 mb-3">Hollow Metal Doors</h3>
      <p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">
        Cost-effective and durable for interior and secondary entrances with fire-rating options and impact resistance.
      </p>

      <h3 class="font-heading text-2xl tracking-wide text-primary mt-8 mb-3">Automatic Sliding and Swing Doors</h3>
      <p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">
        Provide convenience and accessibility for high-traffic commercial spaces.
      </p>

      <h2 class="font-heading text-3xl tracking-wide text-primary mt-10 mb-4">Key Features to Look For</h2>

      <h3 class="font-heading text-2xl tracking-wide text-primary mt-8 mb-3">Security</h3>
      <p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">
        Heavy-duty frames, multi-point locking systems, reinforced hinges, and commercial-grade hardware.
      </p>

      <h3 class="font-heading text-2xl tracking-wide text-primary mt-8 mb-3">Energy Efficiency</h3>
      <p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">
        Properly insulated doors can significantly reduce your heating and cooling costs.
      </p>

      <h3 class="font-heading text-2xl tracking-wide text-primary mt-8 mb-3">ADA Compliance</h3>
      <p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">
        A legal requirement for businesses serving the public.
      </p>

      <h3 class="font-heading text-2xl tracking-wide text-primary mt-8 mb-3">Durability and Low Maintenance</h3>
      <p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">
        Choose materials resistant to rust, corrosion, and fading.
      </p>

      <div class="mt-12 p-6 bg-gray-light rounded-lg text-center">
        <p class="text-gray-600 mb-4">Top Notch Doors & Windows specializes in <a href="/" class="text-primary hover:underline">commercial door installation</a> and replacement across Florida and New York.</p>
        <a href="/contact-us" class="inline-flex bg-primary text-white font-heading text-lg tracking-wide px-6 py-3 rounded hover:bg-black transition-colors">
          GET A FREE ESTIMATE
        </a>
      </div>

      <div class="mt-8 text-sm text-gray-500">
        <p>Related: <a href="/" class="text-primary hover:underline">Sliding Door Repair Services</a> | <a href="/about-us" class="text-primary hover:underline">About Our Team</a> | <a href="/contact-us" class="text-primary hover:underline">Contact Us</a></p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </article>

  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "BlogPosting",
    "headline": "New Commercial Doors: What to Look For When Upgrading Your Business Entrance",
    "datePublished": "2026-03-05",
    "dateModified": "2026-03-05",
    "author": { "@type": "Organization", "name": "Top Notch Doors & Windows" },
    "publisher": { "@type": "Organization", "name": "Top Notch Doors & Windows", "logo": { "@type": "ImageObject", "url": "https://topnotchdoorsandwindows.com/images/logo.png" } },
    "mainEntityOfPage": { "@type": "WebPage", "@id": "https://topnotchdoorsandwindows.com/blog/new-commercial-doors-what-to-look-for-when-upgrading-your-business-entrance" }
  })} />
</Layout>
